reason.tex:
\begin{align}
\lim_{x\to 0} f(x) &= \lim_{x\to 0}\left(\sin x-\cos x\right)  \\
&= 0-1 = -1 = f(0) 
\end{align}
%text

And as $\lim_{x\to 0}f(x) = f(0)$, therefore
$f(x)$ is \underline\text{continuous at $x=0$}

Moreover, $f(x)$ is continuous when 
$x\neq 0$. Therefore, $f(x)$ is continuous
\underline\text{for all $x$} 
%
